  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Centre Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct administrative and operational tasks at the centre</li>\n  <li>Work towards attaining student sign-up targets and maximise monthly retention</li>\n  <li>Liaise with customers and respond promptly to queries</li>\n  <li>Resolve any customer grievances in a courteous and professional manner</li>\n  <li>Assist with customer payments and maintain accurate files for auditing</li>\n  <li>Assist with performance reviews and student promotions</li>\n  <li>Update HQ promptly about student enrolment, trial lessons, and student withdrawal</li>\n  <li>Handle petty cash at centre</li>\n  <li>Safeguarding student welfare and safety</li>\n  <li>Ensure the centre is well-maintained with a high standard of cleanliness</li>\n  <li>Ensure all classrooms are well stocked with required materials and stationery</li>\n  <li>Assist with any other ad hoc projects</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Experience and Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma-level qualification or higher</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of relevant work experience preferably in Education, Retail, Airlines, or any other customer-centric industries</li>\n  <li>Good command of English – both spoken and written</li>\n  <li>Kind and nurturing when interacting with children</li>\n  <li>Professional and courteous when communicating with parents/guardians</li>\n  <li>Excellent organisation skills</li>\n  <li>Proficient with MS Office and Excel</li>\n  <li>Willing to work both weekends and three weekdays</li>\n  <li>Experienced candidates will be considered for the Centre Manager position.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Company Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Medical and dental benefits</li>\n  <li>Birthday leave</li>\n  <li>Incentive program</li>\n</ul>",
